{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Bacteria are the oldest living organisms on the earth."},{"time":3000,"text":"They've been here for billions of years,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and what they are are single-celled microscopic organisms."},{"time":9000,"text":"So they are one cell and they have this special property"},{"time":12000,"text":"that they only have one piece of DNA."},{"time":14000,"text":"They have very few genes,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and genetic information to encode all of the traits that they carry out."},{"time":20000,"text":"And the way bacteria make a living"},{"time":22000,"text":"is that they consume nutrients from the environment,"},{"time":25000,"text":"they grow to twice their size, they cut themselves down in the middle,"},{"time":28000,"text":"and one cell becomes two, and so on and so on."},{"time":31000,"text":"They just grow and divide, and grow and divide -- so a kind of boring life,"},{"time":35000,"text":"except that what I would argue is that you have"},{"time":37000,"text":"an amazing interaction with these critters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"I know you guys think of yourself as humans, and this is sort of how I think of you."},{"time":43000,"text":"This man is supposed to represent"},{"time":45000,"text":"a generic human being,"},{"time":47000,"text":"and all of the circles in that man are all of the cells that make up your body."},{"time":51000,"text":"There is about a trillion human cells that make each one of us"},{"time":54000,"text":"who we are and able to do all the things that we do,"},{"time":57000,"text":"but you have 10 trillion bacterial cells"},{"time":60000,"text":"in you or on you at any moment in your life."},{"time":62000,"text":"So, 10 times more bacterial cells"},{"time":64000,"text":"than human cells on a human being."},{"time":67000,"text":"And of course it's the DNA that counts,"},{"time":69000,"text":"so here's all the A, T, Gs and Cs"},{"time":71000,"text":"that make up your genetic code, and give you all your charming characteristics."},{"time":74000,"text":"You have about 30,000 genes."},{"time":76000,"text":"Well it turns out you have 100 times more bacterial genes"},{"time":79000,"text":"playing a role in you or on you all of your life."},{"time":83000,"text":"At the best, you're 10 percent human,"},{"time":86000,"text":"but more likely about one percent human,"},{"time":88000,"text":"depending on which of these metrics you like."},{"time":90000,"text":"I know you think of yourself as human beings,"},{"time":92000,"text":"but I think of you as 90 or 99 percent bacterial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"These bacteria are not passive riders,"},{"time":100000,"text":"these are incredibly important, they keep us alive."},{"time":103000,"text":"They cover us in an invisible body armor"},{"time":106000,"text":"that keeps environmental insults out"},{"time":108000,"text":"so that we stay healthy."},{"time":110000,"text":"They digest our food, they make our vitamins,"},{"time":112000,"text":"they actually educate your immune system"},{"time":114000,"text":"to keep bad microbes out."},{"time":116000,"text":"So they do all these amazing things"},{"time":118000,"text":"that help us and are vital for keeping us alive,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and they never get any press for that."},{"time":124000,"text":"But they get a lot of press because they do a lot of"},{"time":126000,"text":"terrible things as well."},{"time":128000,"text":"So, there's all kinds of bacteria on the Earth"},{"time":131000,"text":"that have no business being in you or on you at any time,"},{"time":134000,"text":"and if they are, they make you incredibly sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"And so, the question for my lab is whether you want to think about all the"},{"time":141000,"text":"good things that bacteria do, or all the bad things that bacteria do."},{"time":145000,"text":"The question we had is how could they do anything at all?"},{"time":147000,"text":"I mean they're incredibly small,"},{"time":149000,"text":"you have to have a microscope to see one."},{"time":151000,"text":"They live this sort of boring life where they grow and divide,"},{"time":154000,"text":"and they've always been considered to be these asocial reclusive organisms."},{"time":159000,"text":"And so it seemed to us that they are just too small to have an impact"},{"time":162000,"text":"on the environment"},{"time":164000,"text":"if they simply act as individuals."},{"time":166000,"text":"And so we wanted to think if there couldn't be a different"},{"time":168000,"text":"way that bacteria live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"The clue to this came from another marine bacterium,"},{"time":174000,"text":"and it's a bacterium called Vibrio fischeri."},{"time":177000,"text":"What you're looking at on this slide is just a person from my lab"},{"time":180000,"text":"holding a flask of a liquid culture of a bacterium,"},{"time":183000,"text":"a harmless beautiful bacterium that comes from the ocean,"},{"time":186000,"text":"named Vibrio fischeri."},{"time":188000,"text":"This bacterium has the special property that it makes light,"},{"time":191000,"text":"so it makes bioluminescence,"},{"time":193000,"text":"like fireflies make light."},{"time":195000,"text":"We're not doing anything to the cells here."},{"time":197000,"text":"We just took the picture by turning the lights off in the room,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and this is what we see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"What was actually interesting to us"},{"time":203000,"text":"was not that the bacteria made light,"},{"time":205000,"text":"but when the bacteria made light."},{"time":207000,"text":"What we noticed is when the bacteria were alone,"},{"time":210000,"text":"so when they were in dilute suspension, they made no light."},{"time":213000,"text":"But when they grew to a certain cell number"},{"time":215000,"text":"all the bacteria turned on light simultaneously."},{"time":219000,"text":"The question that we had is how can bacteria, these primitive organisms,"},{"time":223000,"text":"tell the difference from times when they're alone,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and times when they're in a community,"},{"time":227000,"text":"and then all do something together."},{"time":230000,"text":"What we've figured out is that the way that they do that is that they talk to each other,"},{"time":234000,"text":"and they talk with a chemical language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"This is now supposed to be my bacterial cell."},{"time":239000,"text":"When it's alone it doesn't make any light."},{"time":242000,"text":"But what it does do is to make and secrete small molecules"},{"time":246000,"text":"that you can think of like hormones,"},{"time":248000,"text":"and these are the red triangles, and when the bacteria is alone"},{"time":251000,"text":"the molecules just float away and so no light."},{"time":254000,"text":"But when the bacteria grow and double"},{"time":256000,"text":"and they're all participating in making these molecules,"},{"time":259000,"text":"the molecule -- the extracellular amount of that molecule"},{"time":263000,"text":"increases in proportion to cell number."},{"time":266000,"text":"And when the molecule hits a certain amount"},{"time":268000,"text":"that tells the bacteria how many neighbors there are,"},{"time":271000,"text":"they recognize that molecule"},{"time":273000,"text":"and all of the bacteria turn on light in synchrony."},{"time":276000,"text":"That's how bioluminescence works --"},{"time":278000,"text":"they're talking with these chemical words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"The reason that Vibrio fischeri is doing that comes from the biology."},{"time":284000,"text":"Again, another plug for the animals in the ocean,"},{"time":287000,"text":"Vibrio fischeri lives in this squid."},{"time":290000,"text":"What you are looking at is the Hawaiian Bobtail Squid,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and it's been turned on its back,"},{"time":294000,"text":"and what I hope you can see are these two glowing lobes"},{"time":297000,"text":"and these house the Vibrio fischeri cells,"},{"time":300000,"text":"they live in there, at high cell number"},{"time":302000,"text":"that molecule is there, and they're making light."},{"time":304000,"text":"The reason the squid is willing to put up with these shenanigans"},{"time":307000,"text":"is because it wants that light."},{"time":309000,"text":"The way that this symbiosis works"},{"time":311000,"text":"is that this little squid lives just off the coast of Hawaii,"},{"time":315000,"text":"just in sort of shallow knee-deep water."},{"time":317000,"text":"The squid is nocturnal, so during the day"},{"time":320000,"text":"it buries itself in the sand and sleeps,"},{"time":322000,"text":"but then at night it has to come out to hunt."},{"time":325000,"text":"On bright nights when there is lots of starlight or moonlight"},{"time":327000,"text":"that light can penetrate the depth of the water"},{"time":330000,"text":"the squid lives in, since it's just in those couple feet of water."},{"time":333000,"text":"What the squid has developed is a shutter"},{"time":336000,"text":"that can open and close over this specialized light organ housing the bacteria."},{"time":340000,"text":"Then it has detectors on its back"},{"time":342000,"text":"so it can sense how much starlight or moonlight is hitting its back."},{"time":346000,"text":"And it opens and closes the shutter"},{"time":348000,"text":"so the amount of light coming out of the bottom --"},{"time":350000,"text":"which is made by the bacterium --"},{"time":352000,"text":"exactly matches how much light hits the squid's back,"},{"time":354000,"text":"so the squid doesn't make a shadow."},{"time":356000,"text":"It actually uses the light from the bacteria"},{"time":359000,"text":"to counter-illuminate itself in an anti-predation device"},{"time":362000,"text":"so predators can't see its shadow,"},{"time":364000,"text":"calculate its trajectory, and eat it."},{"time":366000,"text":"This is like the stealth bomber of the ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"But then if you think about it, the squid has this terrible problem"},{"time":373000,"text":"because it's got this dying, thick culture of bacteria"},{"time":376000,"text":"and it can't sustain that."},{"time":378000,"text":"And so what happens is every morning when the sun comes up"},{"time":380000,"text":"the squid goes back to sleep, it buries itself in the sand,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and it's got a pump that's attached to its circadian rhythm,"},{"time":386000,"text":"and when the sun comes up it pumps out like 95 percent of the bacteria."},{"time":391000,"text":"Now the bacteria are dilute, that little hormone molecule is gone,"},{"time":394000,"text":"so they're not making light --"},{"time":396000,"text":"but of course the squid doesn't care. It's asleep in the sand."},{"time":398000,"text":"And as the day goes by the bacteria double,"},{"time":400000,"text":"they release the molecule, and then light comes on"},{"time":403000,"text":"at night, exactly when the squid wants it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"First we figured out how this bacterium does this,"},{"time":409000,"text":"but then we brought the tools of molecular biology to this"},{"time":412000,"text":"to figure out really what's the mechanism."},{"time":414000,"text":"And what we found -- so this is now supposed to be, again, my bacterial cell --"},{"time":418000,"text":"is that Vibrio fischeri has a protein --"},{"time":420000,"text":"that's the red box -- it's an enzyme that makes"},{"time":423000,"text":"that little hormone molecule, the red triangle."},{"time":426000,"text":"And then as the cells grow, they're all releasing that molecule"},{"time":428000,"text":"into the environment, so there's lots of molecule there."},{"time":431000,"text":"And the bacteria also have a receptor on their cell surface"},{"time":435000,"text":"that fits like a lock and key with that molecule."},{"time":438000,"text":"These are just like the receptors on the surfaces of your cells."},{"time":441000,"text":"When the molecule increases to a certain amount --"},{"time":444000,"text":"which says something about the number of cells --"},{"time":446000,"text":"it locks down into that receptor"},{"time":448000,"text":"and information comes into the cells"},{"time":450000,"text":"that tells the cells to turn on"},{"time":452000,"text":"this collective behavior of making light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"Why this is interesting is because in the past decade"},{"time":458000,"text":"we have found that this is not just some anomaly"},{"time":460000,"text":"of this ridiculous, glow-in-the-dark bacterium that lives in the ocean --"},{"time":463000,"text":"all bacteria have systems like this."},{"time":466000,"text":"So now what we understand is that all bacteria can talk to each other."},{"time":469000,"text":"They make chemical words, they recognize those words,"},{"time":472000,"text":"and they turn on group behaviors"},{"time":474000,"text":"that are only successful when all of the cells participate in unison."},{"time":479000,"text":"We have a fancy name for this: we call it quorum sensing."},{"time":482000,"text":"They vote with these chemical votes,"},{"time":484000,"text":"the vote gets counted, and then everybody responds to the vote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"What's important for today's talk"},{"time":490000,"text":"is that we know that there are hundreds of behaviors"},{"time":492000,"text":"that bacteria carry out in these collective fashions."},{"time":495000,"text":"But the one that's probably the most important to you is virulence."},{"time":498000,"text":"It's not like a couple bacteria get in you"},{"time":501000,"text":"and they start secreting some toxins --"},{"time":503000,"text":"you're enormous, that would have no effect on you. You're huge."},{"time":506000,"text":"What they do, we now understand,"},{"time":509000,"text":"is they get in you, they wait, they start growing,"},{"time":512000,"text":"they count themselves with these little molecules,"},{"time":514000,"text":"and they recognize when they have the right cell number"},{"time":516000,"text":"that if all of the bacteria launch their virulence attack together,"},{"time":520000,"text":"they are going to be successful at overcoming an enormous host."},{"time":524000,"text":"Bacteria always control pathogenicity with quorum sensing."},{"time":528000,"text":"That's how it works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"We also then went to look at what are these molecules --"},{"time":533000,"text":"these were the red triangles on my slides before."},{"time":536000,"text":"This is the Vibrio fischeri molecule."},{"time":538000,"text":"This is the word that it talks with."},{"time":540000,"text":"So then we started to look at other bacteria,"},{"time":542000,"text":"and these are just a smattering of the molecules that we've discovered."},{"time":545000,"text":"What I hope you can see"},{"time":547000,"text":"is that the molecules are related."},{"time":549000,"text":"The left-hand part of the molecule is identical"},{"time":551000,"text":"in every single species of bacteria."},{"time":554000,"text":"But the right-hand part of the molecule is a little bit different in every single species."},{"time":558000,"text":"What that does is to confer"},{"time":560000,"text":"exquisite species specificities to these languages."},{"time":564000,"text":"Each molecule fits into its partner receptor and no other."},{"time":568000,"text":"So these are private, secret conversations."},{"time":571000,"text":"These conversations are for intraspecies communication."},{"time":575000,"text":"Each bacteria uses a particular molecule that's its language"},{"time":579000,"text":"that allows it to count its own siblings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"Once we got that far we thought"},{"time":585000,"text":"we were starting to understand that bacteria have these social behaviors."},{"time":588000,"text":"But what we were really thinking about is that most of the time"},{"time":591000,"text":"bacteria don't live by themselves, they live in incredible mixtures,"},{"time":594000,"text":"with hundreds or thousands of other species of bacteria."},{"time":598000,"text":"And that's depicted on this slide. This is your skin."},{"time":601000,"text":"So this is just a picture -- a micrograph of your skin."},{"time":604000,"text":"Anywhere on your body, it looks pretty much like this,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and what I hope you can see is that there's all kinds of bacteria there."},{"time":610000,"text":"And so we started to think if this really is about communication in bacteria,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and it's about counting your neighbors,"},{"time":616000,"text":"it's not enough to be able to only talk within your species."},{"time":619000,"text":"There has to be a way to take a census"},{"time":621000,"text":"of the rest of the bacteria in the population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"So we went back to molecular biology"},{"time":626000,"text":"and started studying different bacteria,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and what we've found now is that"},{"time":630000,"text":"in fact, bacteria are multilingual."},{"time":632000,"text":"They all have a species-specific system --"},{"time":635000,"text":"they have a molecule that says \"me.\""},{"time":637000,"text":"But then, running in parallel to that is a second system"},{"time":640000,"text":"that we've discovered, that's generic."},{"time":642000,"text":"So, they have a second enzyme that makes a second signal"},{"time":645000,"text":"and it has its own receptor,"},{"time":647000,"text":"and this molecule is the trade language of bacteria."},{"time":650000,"text":"It's used by all different bacteria"},{"time":652000,"text":"and it's the language of interspecies communication."},{"time":656000,"text":"What happens is that bacteria are able to count"},{"time":659000,"text":"how many of me and how many of you."},{"time":662000,"text":"They take that information inside,"},{"time":664000,"text":"and they decide what tasks to carry out"},{"time":666000,"text":"depending on who's in the minority and who's in the majority"},{"time":670000,"text":"of any given population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"Then again we turn to chemistry,"},{"time":674000,"text":"and we figured out what this generic molecule is --"},{"time":677000,"text":"that was the pink ovals on my last slide, this is it."},{"time":680000,"text":"It's a very small, five-carbon molecule."},{"time":682000,"text":"What the important thing is that we learned"},{"time":685000,"text":"is that every bacterium has exactly the same enzyme"},{"time":688000,"text":"and makes exactly the same molecule."},{"time":690000,"text":"So they're all using this molecule"},{"time":692000,"text":"for interspecies communication."},{"time":694000,"text":"This is the bacterial Esperanto."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"Once we got that far, we started to learn"},{"time":700000,"text":"that bacteria can talk to each other with this chemical language."},{"time":703000,"text":"But what we started to think is that maybe there is something"},{"time":705000,"text":"practical that we can do here as well."},{"time":707000,"text":"I've told you that bacteria do have all these social behaviors,"},{"time":710000,"text":"they communicate with these molecules."},{"time":713000,"text":"Of course, I've also told you that one of the important things they do"},{"time":716000,"text":"is to initiate pathogenicity using quorum sensing."},{"time":719000,"text":"We thought, what if we made these bacteria"},{"time":721000,"text":"so they can't talk or they can't hear?"},{"time":724000,"text":"Couldn't these be new kinds of antibiotics?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":727000,"text":"Of course, you've just heard and you already know"},{"time":729000,"text":"that we're running out of antibiotics."},{"time":731000,"text":"Bacteria are incredibly multi-drug-resistant right now,"},{"time":734000,"text":"and that's because all of the antibiotics that we use kill bacteria."},{"time":738000,"text":"They either pop the bacterial membrane,"},{"time":740000,"text":"they make the bacterium so it can't replicate its DNA."},{"time":743000,"text":"We kill bacteria with traditional antibiotics"},{"time":746000,"text":"and that selects for resistant mutants."},{"time":748000,"text":"And so now of course we have this global problem"},{"time":751000,"text":"in infectious diseases."},{"time":753000,"text":"We thought, well what if we could sort of do behavior modifications,"},{"time":756000,"text":"just make these bacteria so they can't talk, they can't count,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and they don't know to launch virulence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"And so that's exactly what we've done, and we've sort of taken two strategies."},{"time":765000,"text":"The first one is we've targeted"},{"time":767000,"text":"the intraspecies communication system."},{"time":770000,"text":"So we made molecules that look kind of like the real molecules --"},{"time":773000,"text":"which you saw -- but they're a little bit different."},{"time":775000,"text":"And so they lock into those receptors,"},{"time":777000,"text":"and they jam recognition of the real thing."},{"time":780000,"text":"By targeting the red system,"},{"time":782000,"text":"what we are able to do is to make"},{"time":784000,"text":"species-specific, or disease-specific, anti-quorum sensing molecules."},{"time":789000,"text":"We've also done the same thing with the pink system."},{"time":792000,"text":"We've taken that universal molecule and turned it around a little bit"},{"time":795000,"text":"so that we've made antagonists"},{"time":797000,"text":"of the interspecies communication system."},{"time":799000,"text":"The hope is that these will be used as broad-spectrum antibiotics"},{"time":804000,"text":"that work against all bacteria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"To finish I'll just show you the strategy."},{"time":809000,"text":"In this one I'm just using the interspecies molecule,"},{"time":811000,"text":"but the logic is exactly the same."},{"time":813000,"text":"What you know is that when that bacterium gets into the animal,"},{"time":816000,"text":"in this case, a mouse,"},{"time":818000,"text":"it doesn't initiate virulence right away."},{"time":820000,"text":"It gets in, it starts growing, it starts secreting"},{"time":823000,"text":"its quorum sensing molecules."},{"time":825000,"text":"It recognizes when it has enough bacteria"},{"time":827000,"text":"that now they're going to launch their attack,"},{"time":829000,"text":"and the animal dies."},{"time":831000,"text":"What we've been able to do is to give these virulent infections,"},{"time":834000,"text":"but we give them in conjunction with our anti-quorum sensing molecules --"},{"time":838000,"text":"so these are molecules that look kind of like the real thing,"},{"time":840000,"text":"but they're a little bit different which I've depicted on this slide."},{"time":843000,"text":"What we now know is that if we treat the animal"},{"time":846000,"text":"with a pathogenic bacterium -- a multi-drug-resistant pathogenic bacterium --"},{"time":850000,"text":"in the same time we give our anti-quorum sensing molecule,"},{"time":854000,"text":"in fact, the animal lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"We think that this is the next generation of antibiotics"},{"time":860000,"text":"and it's going to get us around, at least initially,"},{"time":862000,"text":"this big problem of resistance."},{"time":864000,"text":"What I hope you think, is that bacteria can talk to each other,"},{"time":867000,"text":"they use chemicals as their words,"},{"time":870000,"text":"they have an incredibly complicated chemical lexicon"},{"time":873000,"text":"that we're just now starting to learn about."},{"time":875000,"text":"Of course what that allows bacteria to do"},{"time":878000,"text":"is to be multicellular."},{"time":880000,"text":"So in the spirit of TED they're doing things together"},{"time":883000,"text":"because it makes a difference."},{"time":885000,"text":"What happens is that bacteria have these collective behaviors,"},{"time":889000,"text":"and they can carry out tasks"},{"time":891000,"text":"that they could never accomplish"},{"time":893000,"text":"if they simply acted as individuals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"What I would hope that I could further argue to you"},{"time":898000,"text":"is that this is the invention of multicellularity."},{"time":901000,"text":"Bacteria have been on the Earth for billions of years;"},{"time":905000,"text":"humans, couple hundred thousand."},{"time":907000,"text":"We think bacteria made the rules"},{"time":909000,"text":"for how multicellular organization works."},{"time":912000,"text":"We think, by studying bacteria,"},{"time":915000,"text":"we're going to be able to have insight about multicellularity in the human body."},{"time":919000,"text":"We know that the principles and the rules,"},{"time":921000,"text":"if we can figure them out in these sort of primitive organisms,"},{"time":923000,"text":"the hope is that they will be applied"},{"time":925000,"text":"to other human diseases and human behaviors as well."},{"time":929000,"text":"I hope that what you've learned"},{"time":931000,"text":"is that bacteria can distinguish self from other."},{"time":934000,"text":"By using these two molecules they can say \"me\" and they can say \"you.\""},{"time":937000,"text":"Again of course that's what we do,"},{"time":939000,"text":"both in a molecular way,"},{"time":941000,"text":"and also in an outward way,"},{"time":943000,"text":"but I think about the molecular stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":945000,"text":"This is exactly what happens in your body."},{"time":947000,"text":"It's not like your heart cells and your kidney cells get all mixed up every day,"},{"time":950000,"text":"and that's because there's all of this chemistry going on,"},{"time":953000,"text":"these molecules that say who each of these groups of cells is,"},{"time":956000,"text":"and what their tasks should be."},{"time":958000,"text":"Again, we think that bacteria invented that,"},{"time":961000,"text":"and you've just evolved a few more bells and whistles,"},{"time":964000,"text":"but all of the ideas are in these simple systems that we can study."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968000,"text":"The final thing is, again just to reiterate that there's this practical part,"},{"time":972000,"text":"and so we've made these anti-quorum sensing molecules"},{"time":975000,"text":"that are being developed as new kinds of therapeutics."},{"time":978000,"text":"But then, to finish with a plug for all the good and miraculous bacteria"},{"time":981000,"text":"that live on the Earth,"},{"time":983000,"text":"we've also made pro-quorum sensing molecules."},{"time":985000,"text":"So, we've targeted those systems to make the molecules work better."},{"time":988000,"text":"Remember you have these 10 times or more bacterial cells"},{"time":992000,"text":"in you or on you, keeping you healthy."},{"time":994000,"text":"What we're also trying to do is to beef up the conversation"},{"time":997000,"text":"of the bacteria that live as mutualists with you,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"in the hopes of making you more healthy,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"making those conversations better,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"so bacteria can do things that we want them to do"},{"time":1007000,"text":"better than they would be on their own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010000,"text":"Finally, I wanted to show you"},{"time":1012000,"text":"this is my gang at Princeton, New Jersey."},{"time":1014000,"text":"Everything I told you about was discovered by someone in that picture."},{"time":1018000,"text":"I hope when you learn things,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"like about how the natural world works --"},{"time":1022000,"text":"I just want to say that whenever you read something in the newspaper"},{"time":1025000,"text":"or you get to hear some talk about something ridiculous in the natural world"},{"time":1028000,"text":"it was done by a child."},{"time":1030000,"text":"Science is done by that demographic."},{"time":1032000,"text":"All of those people are between 20 and 30 years old,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"and they are the engine that drives scientific discovery in this country."},{"time":1040000,"text":"It's a really lucky demographic to work with."},{"time":1043000,"text":"I keep getting older and older and they're always the same age,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"and it's just a crazy delightful job."},{"time":1049000,"text":"I want to thank you for inviting me here."},{"time":1051000,"text":"It's a big treat for me to get to come to this conference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}